## Vanilla JavaScript Patterns

### DOM Selection

```javascript
// Good: Modern selectors
const button = document.getElementById('user-login-submit-button')
const buttons = document.querySelectorAll('.btn-primary')
const firstCard = document.querySelector('.card')

// Bad: jQuery (not needed)
// const button = $('#user-login-submit-button')
```

### Event Listeners

```javascript
// Good: addEventListener
const button = document.getElementById('submit-button')
button.addEventListener('click', (event) => {
  event.preventDefault()
  handleSubmit()
})

// Good: Event delegation for dynamic content
document.addEventListener('click', (event) => {
  if (event.target.matches('[data-action="delete"]')) {
    handleDelete(event.target)
  }
})

// Bad: Inline onclick
// <button onclick="handleClick()">
```

### DOM Manipulation

```javascript
// Good: Modern DOM methods
const element = document.getElementById('article-title')

// Add/remove classes
element.classList.add('active')
element.classList.remove('hidden')
element.classList.toggle('expanded')

// Change content
element.textContent = 'New Title'
element.innerHTML = '<strong>Bold Title</strong>'

// Attributes
element.setAttribute('data-status', 'active')
element.getAttribute('data-id')
element.removeAttribute('disabled')

// Create elements
const div = document.createElement('div')
div.id = 'new-container'
div.className = 'bg-white rounded-lg p-6'
div.textContent = 'Content'

// Append to DOM
document.getElementById('articles-list').appendChild(div)

// Insert at specific position
element.insertAdjacentHTML('beforeend', '<p>New paragraph</p>')
```

